00:23:54.860 --> 00:24:01.180
Of course, I'm going to sit here and say pick the right partner, but it really does make sense, whether it's fourTheorem or some other partner.

372
00:24:01.600 --> 00:24:03.980
Find somebody who does this as their bread and butter.

373
00:24:03.980 --> 00:24:06.640
These are not trivial things to do.

374
00:24:06.760 --> 00:24:07.980
They're hard projects.

375
00:24:08.540 --> 00:24:17.580
But when you talk to somebody like ourselves that we've been doing this now in this particular environment for seven or eight years, you know, we see a lot of repeat problems.

376
00:24:17.720 --> 00:24:23.660
The industries might change, but the gnarly part stays very similar across the individual things.

377
00:24:23.660 --> 00:24:26.160
We can help them identify those quick wins.

378
00:24:26.720 --> 00:24:36.480
And then also we can go in there and work with the team and do that valuable upskilling, leaving them at the end, of course, with still with our jobs intact, but much more interesting jobs now.

379
00:24:37.020 --> 00:24:40.460
You know, you remember that project where we deleted 70 percent of their code base.

380
00:24:40.920 --> 00:24:45.860
You know, when you're not maintaining when you're maintaining a code base, it's only 30 percent of its original size.

381
00:24:45.860 --> 00:24:48.660
That leaves you a lot of time to help innovate.

382
00:24:49.000 --> 00:24:52.440
To be more impacting on the business and to have a more interesting job.

383
00:24:52.780 --> 00:24:54.660
So they'll retain their people.

384
00:24:54.740 --> 00:24:59.900
They'll upskill their people and they'll be they'll be ready for the next disruptor that comes along.

385
00:24:59.900 --> 00:25:02.580
The ones that put their head in the sand and go, do you know what?

386
00:25:02.620 --> 00:25:05.820
I bought that big on prem upgrade two years ago.

387
00:25:05.920 --> 00:25:06.740
I'll wait till it dies.

388
00:25:06.860 --> 00:25:08.820
I have another five or six years to run about it.

389
00:25:09.100 --> 00:25:16.600
They're going to wake up one day and find that there's another revolution or something has come along that's completely going to eat their lunch and leave them in a panic mode.

390
00:25:17.240 --> 00:25:18.600
And that's not the way to do it.

391
00:25:18.600 --> 00:25:35.500
OK, since we're talking about AWS partnering, obviously, fourTheorem is known as a top AWS partner.

