00:25:36.820 --> 00:25:38.060
There's a lot of work out there to be done.

394
00:25:38.320 --> 00:25:45.140
So a lot of people out there, especially our listeners, right, might be thinking of either freelancing or starting off their own cloud consultancy.

395
00:25:45.140 --> 00:25:49.580
What advice can we impart, specifically you, Fiona?

396
00:25:49.800 --> 00:25:52.380
Do you have any tips, tricks, warnings to share?

397
00:25:53.460 --> 00:25:58.440
Well, all the earlier warnings about, you know, setting up your business and cash flow, right, and investment.

398
00:25:58.780 --> 00:26:01.160
Take that as, you know, the first stuff to do.

399
00:26:01.660 --> 00:26:06.960
But if you're thinking, let's imagine you're already out there, you know, and you think, oh, I'm going to become an AWS partner.

400
00:26:07.100 --> 00:26:07.860
This will be great.

401
00:26:08.600 --> 00:26:11.080
And I give a bit of advice around that.

402
00:26:11.080 --> 00:26:19.200
And I think, you know, first and foremostly, and to be fair, AWS tell you this out the gate, you know, they're not going to fill your sales pipeline.

403
00:26:19.680 --> 00:26:24.080
Well, of course, you do think when you become a partner that they will fill your sales pipeline.

404
00:26:24.480 --> 00:26:24.940
And they do.

405
00:26:25.060 --> 00:26:27.820
They have because you look, they have loads of these account management teams.

406
00:26:28.380 --> 00:26:32.280
But they are never going to fully get you in the way that you get your own business.

407
00:26:32.280 --> 00:26:39.440
So if you become a partner, understand that you have to, you have to, first of all, you've got to be responsible for your own sales process.

408
00:26:39.640 --> 00:26:46.560
So becoming a partner from AWS or Azure or anybody else isn't going to solve your new business pipeline piece.

409
00:26:46.980 --> 00:26:48.540
You have to solve that for yourself.

410
00:26:49.060 --> 00:26:54.380
Once you accept that, then you can really lean in and you can leverage these partnerships to the best of their ability.

411
00:26:54.820 --> 00:26:59.880
Bearing in mind that you will almost always be smaller than these huge, big organizations.

412
00:26:59.880 --> 00:27:02.380
So there's going to be a level of bureaucracy.

413
00:27:02.600 --> 00:27:06.800
You'll deal with some wonderful people, but the system and the process will be very frustrating.

414
00:27:07.480 --> 00:27:16.160
They'll have rules, you know, AWS funding rules can be like looking at health care plans in Ireland where you're going, I don't know how to compare one with the next.

415
00:27:16.700 --> 00:27:20.080
You can get very caught up with, you know, trying to keep up with it.

416
00:27:20.180 --> 00:27:22.420
And they do a great job of selling their programs.

417
00:27:22.420 --> 00:27:30.060
But make sure that if you are going to attach yourself with a program, if you keep coming back to first principles and saying, is this the right thing for me?

418
00:27:30.260 --> 00:27:36.540
Because they will require a lot of investment on your part in accreditations and upskilling your teams and getting pieces of paper.

419
00:27:36.980 --> 00:27:40.420
And if that's right for your business, do it for sure.

420
00:27:40.900 --> 00:27:43.500
But make sure you've validated that up first.

421
00:27:43.580 --> 00:27:45.740
And you think, OK, these are very good skill sets.

422
00:27:45.860 --> 00:27:47.160
I want all my team to have them.

423
00:27:47.240 --> 00:27:49.360
Don't do them because it ticks a box in a program.

424
00:27:49.360 --> 00:27:56.540
Do them because they're right for you and make sure that throughout everything you do, that you keep coming back to your own customer obsession.

425
00:27:56.760 --> 00:28:02.200
You know, AWS is customer obsessed, but you need to be even more focused on your own customer obsession.

426
00:28:02.380 --> 00:28:04.960
You are not AWS or Azure or any of these other people.

427
00:28:05.280 --> 00:28:07.740
You are fundamentally your own independent consultancy.

428
00:28:08.140 --> 00:28:09.800
And that's what your clients are relying on, right?

